{
  "stem": "8784.5",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And after seven days of walking on foot, riding with horses, feeding ourselves by stealing and begging, we arrived in Wroclaw, Poland, where the city of Wroclaw was totally destroyed by the bombings.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And when we arrived there, we-- in fact, in that city we were able to sell the two horses that never belong to us anyway.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "But we were able to sell them to have some pennies to get on a train from there on to go to Krakow.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And from Wroclaw to Krakow, we went by train to when we arrived in Krakow a few days later.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And it must have still been June-- early June when I arrived in Krakow.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And upon arrival in Krakow, this was probably one of my saddest days, because here I am in the city of Krakow, no place to go.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "I have absolutely no knowledge of how you go about finding anybody, any family.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I would have to go back to-- to my home and see if anybody arrived there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But immediately-- right there and then-- thinking about it from Czechoslovakia, this was all possible.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "You go and look.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "But when I arrived in the city, I all of the sudden found myself alone, and more so because in that group of 17 people, mostly everybody found a place to go to.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "I actually wound up on the street of Krakow with almost no place to go, until one of the people that was with me together on the transport offers that I better go with her until I find something.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "So when I got to the city was a-- city of Krakow was an extremely sad moment.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "I almost felt like this was all in vain because it doesn't look like I'll be finding anybody.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
